        <etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, заключает <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                                        ><lang/><w>pāy-</w><gloss><q>охранять</q></gloss></mentioned>
                и восходит к %i*рауаvan-%i; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                        ><lang/><w>pā-van</w></mentioned> в <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                                ><lang/><w>xsaϑra-pāvan-</w><gloss><q>сатрап</q></gloss></mentioned>.
                Возможно также, что %i-aw%i — вторичный формант, как в <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æǧdaw"/> ‘обычай’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wæzzaw"/>
                ‘тяжелый’. Удвоение %ij%i — в результате наращения форманта (<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_РОСл."/><biblScope>599</biblScope></bibl>). Ослабление
                гласного (%i*faj-%i — %ifæj-%i) при деривации также закономерно (<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_РОСл."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">598
                                сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">598 ff.</biblScope></bibl>).
                Глагол %i*pō(у)-%i, %iрā(у)%i ‘охранять’ и его производные хорошо представлены в
                индоевропейских языках, в частности в значении ‘пастух’. Приведем только некоторые
                параллели: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pāyīdan:
                                pāy-</w><gloss><q>стеречь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>subān,
                        čūbān</w><gloss><q>пастух</q></gloss></mentioned><note n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE
                </note> (из %ifšu-pāna-%i, где %ifšu-%i ‘овца’, а %ipāna-%i от уже известного
                глагола %iрā(у)-%i ‘охранять’), <mentioned xml:lang="oru"
                                        ><lang/><w>pōy-</w><gloss><q>заботиться</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="oru"><w/><gloss><q>пасти</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>рūу-</w><gloss><q>стеречь</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="oru"
                        ><lang/><w>pay-</w><gloss><q>пасти</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>pōwul:
                        pīāy-</w><gloss><q>пасти</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                                ><lang/><w>*pāy-
                        (p'у-)</w><gloss><q>стеречь</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                                        ><w/><gloss><q>оберегать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"
                        ><w>*pāyāk(pʼyʼk)</w><gloss><q>оберегающий</q></gloss></mentioned>, (согд.
                %i*pōyak%i относится к ос. %ifæjjaw%i, как согд. %i*āγδāk%i к ос. %iæǧdaw%i),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>pā-,
                                pai-</w><gloss><q>охранять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="peo"
                        ><lang/><w>pā-</w><gloss><q>охранять</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="peo"><w/><gloss><q>оберегать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="peo"><w>pātuv</w><gloss><q>пусть
                оберегает</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                                        ><lang/><w>рā(у)-</w><gloss><q>стеречь</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>охранять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>ограждать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w>pāyu-</w><gloss><q>защитник</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>покровитель</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>пастырь</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                        ><lang/><w>рā(у)-</w><gloss><q>стеречь</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>охранять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>присматривать</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>наблюдать</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                        ><w>pāyu-</w><gloss><q>защитник</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>хранитель</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>pёmů</w><gloss><q>пастух</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                        ><lang/><w>ποιμήν</w><gloss><q>пастух</q></gloss></mentioned>. Сюда же
                некоторые относят <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><lang/><w>пасти</w></mentioned> и пр. От
                того же корня %ipā-%i на основе значения ‘ограждать’, ‘служить оградой, щитом’
                образовалось ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæjnæg"/> ‘доска’.%n<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>56</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">It probably includes <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                                        ><lang/><w>pāy-</w><gloss><q>guard</q></gloss></mentioned>
                and traces back to %i*рауаvan-%i; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                                ><lang/><w>pā-van</w></mentioned> in <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                                ><lang/><w>xsaϑra-pāvan-</w><gloss><q>satrap</q></gloss></mentioned>.
                It is also probable that %i-aw%i is a secondary formant, as in <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æǧdaw"/> ‘custom’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wæzzaw"/>
                ‘heavy’. The doubling of %ij%i is the result of formant augmentation (<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_РОСл."/><biblScope>599</biblScope></bibl>). The vowel
                weakening (%i*faj-%i — %ifæj-%i) during the derivation is also regular (<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_РОСл."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">598
                                сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">598 ff.</biblScope></bibl>).
                The verb %i*pō(у)-%i, %iрā(у)%i ‘guard’ and its derivatives are well represented in
                Indo-European languages, particularly, in the meaning ‘shepherd’. Here are some
                parallels: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pāyīdan:
                                pāy-</w><gloss><q>guard</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>subān,
                        čūbān</w><gloss><q>shepherd</q></gloss></mentioned><note n="1"> PUT NOTE
                        HERE </note> (from %ifšu-pāna-%i, where %ifšu-%i means ‘sheep’, and
                %ipāna-%i is from already familiar verb %iрā(у)-%i ‘guard’), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="oru"
                        ><lang/><w>pōy-</w><gloss><q>заботиться</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="oru"><w/><gloss><q>herd (v.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>рūу-</w><gloss><q>guard</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/><w>pay-</w><gloss><q>herd
                        (v.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>pōwul:
                                pīāy-</w><gloss><q>herd (v.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*pāy-
                        (p'у-)</w><gloss><q>guard</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                                        ><w/><gloss><q>protect</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"
                        ><w>*pāyāk(pʼyʼk)</w><gloss><q>protecting</q></gloss></mentioned>, (Sogdian
                %i*pōyak%i is related to Ossetic %ifæjjaw%i, as Sogdian %i*āγδāk%i is related to
                Ossetic %iæǧdaw%i), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>pā-,
                                        pai-</w><gloss><q>guard</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="peo"
                        ><lang/><w>pā-</w><gloss><q>guard</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="peo"><w/><gloss><q>protect</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="peo"><w>pātuv</w><gloss><q>let him
                protect</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                                        ><lang/><w>рā(у)-</w><gloss><q>guard</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>safeguard</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>enclose</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w>pāyu-</w><gloss><q>protector</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>patron</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>shepherd</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                        ><lang/><w>рā(у)-</w><gloss><q>guard</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>guard</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>look after</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>watch</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w>pāyu-</w><gloss><q>guardian</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>protector</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="lt"
                        ><lang/><w>pёmů</w><gloss><q>shepherd</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="grc"
                        ><lang/><w>ποιμήν</w><gloss><q>shepherd</q></gloss></mentioned>. Some people
                also connect it with <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><lang/><w>herd (v.)</w></mentioned>
                etc. From the same root %ipā-%i the Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæjnæg"/>
                ‘plank’ was derived on the basis of meanings ‘protect’, ‘serve as a fence, as a
                                shield’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                        /><biblScope>56</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
